      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_ChangeCurrentBillingPeriod",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to manage the transition between billing periods within a database system. It retrieves the current and previous billing periods, prepares the system for the next billing period, and inserts a new current billing period. The procedure outputs a status code indicating the success of the operation."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
